Slovenian Central Bank Lifts Capital Ratio Powers, Finance Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-10-13T07:02:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/slovenian-central-bank-lifts-capital-ratio-powers-finance-says.html
The Slovenian central bank will be
able to demand higher  capital requirements  from banks than the
legal minimum, Finance newspaper  reported , citing lawmakers.  The central bank, led by Governor Marko Kranjec, will also
have expanded authority to limit executive compensation of
bankers in case of poor capital adequacy ratios after lawmakers
passed new legislation on the banking industry, the Ljubljana-
based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana, Slovenia, at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  